                "Section 6(l)(1) of RESPA, discussed previously, establishes that servicers must use first-class mail to send the notices established by section 6(l)(1)(A) and (B) of RESPA. The Bureau proposed to implement this aspect of section 6(l)(1) of RESPA by adding new \u00a7 1024.37(f) to provide that if a servicer mails a notice required pursuant to \u00a7 1024.37(c)(1)(i), (d)(1), or (e)(1) of this section, a servicer must use a class of mail not less than first-class mail.",
